Ogun State governor, Dapo Abiodun, has sworn-in 19 commissioners with a stern warning to steer off allegiance to any god-fatherism or risk being disgraced out of office. Abiodun gave the warning during the swearing-in ceremony of the newly appointed commissioners held yesterday at the June 12 Cultural Centre, Abeokuta, the state capital. The governor, who also swore-in 16 special advisers, emphatically declared that the new commissioners must be accountable to the people of the state who are at the receiving end of their performance as none of the perceived godfathers was responsible for their emergence. Abiodun urged the new commissioners to be good ambassadors of his administration values of fairness, equity and justice and remain connected to the people. He, therefore, urged them to be “steadfast, prudent, accountable” as well as efficiently integrate their visions into the programmes of his administration’s “building our future together. “Today, I want to challenge you with new leadership and the responsibility to improve the lives and transformation who need you the most. This is the ideal that motivates our administration and why we have employed the service of professionals, experienced individual who shared the vision and passion and development of our dear state.